Fetch gawk sources from http://savannah.gnu.org/projects/gawk/

To compile for arm (Note: gnu abi and not android abi):
./configure --host=arm-linux-gnueabi --enable-static --disable-shared LDFLAGS=-static CC="arm-linux-gnueabi-gcc-5"
make

To compile for x86 (Note that you cannot have gcc-multilib installed together with arm-linux-gnueabi):
./configure --enable-static --disable-shared "CFLAGS=-m32" "CPPFLAGS=-m32" "CXXFLAGS=-m32" "LDFLAGS=-static -m32"
make "LDFLAGS=-static -m32"

The gawk binary can be found in the main folder

gawk is part of the GNU Project and is licensed under the GPLv3 or later
